<txt>
Version 1.0 (March 2010)
<p></p>
<a href="https://github.com/pvermees/helioplot/blob/4a96f61a377d70a9e888e3b77417491118a949b3/dist/HelioPlot.1.1.jar?raw=true">Version 1.1</a> (January 2013)<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;- Fonts scale with the size of the plot window, and are embedded
in the PDF file. Tip: to produce the best graphical output, maximize your
plot window and save as PDF.<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;- The program remembers the input directory, thus saving time when processing
multiple input files.
<p></p>
<a href="https://github.com/pvermees/helioplot/blob/4a96f61a377d70a9e888e3b77417491118a949b3/dist/HelioPlot.1.2.jar?raw=true">Version 1.2</a> (August 2013)<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;- Higher resolution graphics.<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;- Ability to save plot in <tt>.png</tt> format on Mac and Linux.
<p></p>
<a href="https://github.com/pvermees/helioplot/blob/4a96f61a377d70a9e888e3b77417491118a949b3/dist/HelioPlot.1.3.jar?raw=true">Version 1.3</a> (January 2014)<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;- Fixes a problem in which some of the contours partially plotted outside the ternary diagram.<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;- Age labels on the top of the logratio plot no longer overlap.<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;- The input table automatically switches from 7 to 9 columns when Sm 
is present in (but colour labels are absent from) the input file.<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(update based on feedback from Kalin McDannell).
<p></p>
<a href="https://github.com/pvermees/helioplot/blob/4a96f61a377d70a9e888e3b77417491118a949b3/dist/HelioPlot.1.4.jar?raw=true">Version 1.4</a> (February 2014)<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;- Fixed a minor bug caused by the previous upgrade, which in some cases caused 
the program to stop after drawing the age contours.<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;- Ellipse colours are now always taken from the ninth input column unless the latter is empty.<br>
<p></p>
<a href="https://github.com/pvermees/helioplot/blob/4a96f61a377d70a9e888e3b77417491118a949b3/dist/HelioPlot.1.5.jar?raw=true">Version 1.5</a> (March 2014)<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;- Automatically checks for updates.<br>
<p></p>
<a href="https://github.com/pvermees/helioplot/blob/4a96f61a377d70a9e888e3b77417491118a949b3/dist/HelioPlot.2.0.jar?raw=true">Version 2.0</a> (September 2014)<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;- Ternary plots are scaled by normalising to the geometric mean composition [Von Eynatten et al., 2002].<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;- Improved error propagation of individual analyses.<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;- Automatic scaling of freshly pasted data.<br>
<p></p>
<a href=".jar?raw=true">Version 2.1</a> (March 2016)<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;- Source code available from <a href="https://github.com/pvermees/helioplot">github</a><br>
</txt>
</div>
